# Inventory Service

This microservice manages event inventory for ticket sales.  
It provides CRUD operations for events and a reservation endpoint to decrement available tickets atomically.

## Endpoints
- GET /api/events — list all events  
- GET /api/events/{id} — get one event  
- POST /api/events — create an event  
- PUT /api/events/{id} — update event  
- DELETE /api/events/{id} — delete event  
- PUT /api/events/reserve/{eventId}?quantity={x} — reserve tickets atomically

## Technologies
- Spring Boot 3.5.7
- Java 17
- H2 Database
- JPA / Lombok

## How to Run
1. Open in IntelliJ
2. Run `InventoryServiceApplication.java`
3. App runs on `http://localhost:8081`
4. Test using Postman or Curl

## Example Request
POST /api/events
{
  "name": "Concert A",
  "location": "UL Arena",
  "date": "2025-12-15",
  "availableTickets": 50,
  "price": 39.99
}
